tags.description: Today Barron is one of the most intact ghost towns in the state. There are several standing cabins and an equal number of collapsed ones. You don’t have to look hard to find several mining shafts/entrances, many of which are still explorable.
tags.name: Barron
tags.note: The best time of year to visit is between mid-July and late September when there is no snow cover to worry about. Barron can be accessed by turning off of highway 20 at the town of Mazama, then driving north on road 9140 for 8.8 miles.

tags.description: Restricted access for property owners only.  Trinty (Which is at the end of the Chiwawa River Road) was a large copper mine settlement and died out in about 1938.

tags.description: The Old Molson Ghost Town Museum is an outdoor collection of pioneer buildings and equipment. This outdoor museum exhibit was established by Harry Sherling in 1960 in remembrance of the rich pioneering history of Old Molson.  The museum is open Year Round
